  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When account that is recovered had some unread messages, the messages counter appears and stays even though chat was opened and all messages were read. Clearing or deleting the chat does not help. User can't get rid of the unread counter.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/40725608-21892658-6424-11e8-89b1-9088298f857e.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\nIt's worth noting that the recovered chat contains only the received messages. **It does not have messages that have been sent.** It's probably a different issue that we should fix: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4542\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nMessage counter disappears.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nMessage counter shows some unread messages even though chat was opened and all messages that have been sent by another device are visible.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status on device A and B\r\n- Create 1-1 chat between devices\r\n- Send some messages between devices\r\n- Device A: save the account seed and uninstall the app\r\n- Device B: send some messages and request commands to device A\r\n- Device A: recover the account and open the chat\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, May 30 and release/0.9.19 branch\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
